{"parentUuid":null,"isSidechain":true,"promptId":"69d857ed-8551-461b-a7b1-a4471347aa83","agentId":"af77a5a8b6733bcfb","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":"Test file: src/game-of-life.spec.ts\nImplementation file: src/game-of-life.ts\nPassing tests: 3 (plus 4 todo)\nRecent changes: Green phase introduced neighbor counting — `isNeighbor` (Chebyshev distance), `countLiveNeighbors`, and `nextGeneration` filtering live cells with `>= 3` neighbors (minimal rule forced by current tests; upper bound and birth rule intentionally absent).\n\nCurrent implementation:\n```ts\nexport type Cell = [number, number];\n\nconst isNeighbor = ([x, y]: Cell, [otherX, otherY]: Cell): boolean =>\n  Math.abs(x - otherX) <= 1 &&\n  Math.abs(y - otherY) <= 1 &&\n  !(x === otherX && y === otherY);\n\nconst countLiveNeighbors = (cell: Cell, cells: Cell[]): number =>\n  cells.filter((other) => isNeighbor(cell, other)).length;\n\nexport const nextGeneration = (cells: Cell[]): Cell[] =>\n  cells.filter((cell) => countLiveNeighbors(cell, cells) >= 3);\n```\n\nRun tests with `pnpm test` (prefix `NODE_ENV=development` if vitest not found). Keep all tests green. Do not add overpopulation/reproduction logic (future tests will force it).\n\nEXPERIMENT MODE: Run autonomously, proceed to next test after completion."},"uuid":"a9782f2c-d67a-45ee-897e-ba9c199164b9","timestamp":"2026-06-09T23:39:19.771Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"sdk-cli","cwd":"/home/experimenter/experiments/runs/2026-06-09_23-29-15_game-of-life-example-mapping_v4-exact-subagents_fable-5","sessionId":"3fb746c5-8173-46be-bc4c-fbb039330c50","version":"2.1.170","gitBranch":"HEAD"}
